
[1]alarmed

   AL'ARMED, pp. Notified of sudden danger; surprised with fear; roused to
   vigilance or activity by apprehension of approaching danger; solicitous
   at the prospect or expectation of evil. Thus, we are alarmed at the
   approach of danger, or alarmed for the safety of friends at sea.
